= Key Terms / Mappings
- *Holism:* The whole is greater than the sum of its parts
- *Reductionism:* A whole can be understood completely if you under its parts and the nature of their sum
- *Stretto:* One theme repeatedly enters in one voice after another with little delay
- *Teleology:* The explanation of phenomena in terms of the purpose they serve rather than of the cause by which they arise
- *Organ Point*: Sustaining of a single note by one of the voices (often the lowest)

